answerText: Eridanus[10] This ornithological constellation's brightest star, Deneb, forms one vertice of the summer triangle, along with Vega and Altair.  Next to it can be seen its enemy, Vulpecula.

question: Question: For 10 points each, name the following constellations: [10] This sixth largest constellation's brightest star is Achernar and it's the namesake of the largest void in the known universe.  It is also the home of the Witch Head Nebula.
